Outputs (BOTH are required):

1. **Write `DESIGN.md` to disk** at `{{ design_md_path }}` using the `Write` tool.
   Format: design-picker-spec — YAML frontmatter (`name`, `colors`, `typography`,
   `rounded`, `spacing`, `motion`) followed by `## Overview`, `## Colors`,
   `## Typography`, `## Layout`, `## Elevation`, `## Components`,
   `## Do's and Don'ts` prose sections. The downstream beat sub-agents will
   read this file as their source of truth — make every section operational,
   not aspirational.

2. **Return ONLY JSON** matching the `DesignDoc` schema shown below. Substance
   bounds are non-negotiable — the deterministic gate `gate:design_ok` rejects
   anything below them and re-dispatches you with the violation list:
   - `refs` ≥ 2 (named designers, brands, or movements with the specific aspect
     being referenced)
   - `alternatives` ≥ 1 (a real direction you considered and rejected, with a
     concrete reason — not a strawman)
   - `anti_patterns` ≥ 3 (specific don'ts for THIS brand, not generic
     "avoid neon")
   - `beat_visual_mapping` ≥ 1 entry per beat in the EDL — the beat label and a
     one-sentence treatment (palette emphasis, type scale, motion intensity,
     decoratives).

```json
{
  "style_name": "Swiss Pulse",
  "palette": [
    {"role": "background", "hex": "#0a0a0a"},
    {"role": "foreground", "hex": "#f0f0f0"},
    {"role": "accent",     "hex": "#0066FF"}
  ],
  "typography": [
    {"role": "headline", "family": "Helvetica Neue", "weight": 700, "size": "5rem"},
    {"role": "body",     "family": "Inter",          "weight": 400, "size": "1rem"}
  ],
  "refs": [
    {"label": "Josef Müller-Brockmann", "description": "Grid-locked compositions; numeric stats dominate the frame."},
    {"label": "Stripe Press",            "description": "Editorial restraint — large headlines, generous gutters, no decoration for decoration's sake."}
  ],
  "alternatives": [
    {"name": "Folk Frequency", "rejected_because": "Tone is festive/community; this episode reads as analytical and would feel trivialized."}
  ],
  "anti_patterns": [
    "No gradient text — looks like every AI-generated landing page.",
    "No cyan-on-dark or purple-to-blue gradients — neon AI default.",
    "No equal-weight centered layouts — must lead the eye to the stat."
  ],
  "beat_visual_mapping": [
    {"beat": "HOOK",     "treatment": "Tight typographic close-up, accent at full saturation, ambient grid lines breathing."},
    {"beat": "PROBLEM",  "treatment": "Stat at 7rem dominates frame; foreground tinted toward accent at 8% opacity."},
    {"beat": "PAYOFF",   "treatment": "Wide reveal with hairline rules; entrance staggered 120ms; no exit tween, transition handles."}
  ],
  "design_md_path": "{{ design_md_path }}"
}
```

Do not include prose outside the JSON. Hex colors must be CSS-valid (`#RGB`,
`#RRGGBB`, or `#RRGGBBAA`). The HARD-GATE in the canon you just read is real —
if you write `#333` or `Roboto` you have skipped it.
